Remark 9.2 (Three levels of approximation in the correspondence).
The asymptotic correspondence rests on three distinct approximations. (a) Gaussian contraction (G1): the possibility distribution must contract to a Gaussian in ; no claim is made for finite . (b) Linearization (G3)–(G4): the correspondence for nonlinear holds only to first order; higher-order corrections present in the UKF sigma-point architecture are not recovered by the continuous-support limit without additional regularity assumptions. (c) Continuous support: finite Smolyak grids at level introduce discretization errors absent from the UKF’s moment equations. These three qualifications together make the “asymptotic correspondence” label precise: the ESPF and UKF share the same optimal solution in the joint limit, but are not algebraically equivalent under any finite operating condition.
Remark 9.3 (Convergent optimality, not hierarchical containment).
The UKF and ESPF are not in a containment relationship. They solve categorically different problems. The UKF minimizes mean squared error given a stochastic generative model: it asserts truth and quantifies certainty around that assertion. The ESPF minimizes maximum entropy given only evidence compatibility: it eliminates what has been falsified and reports what remains, without asserting where truth is. When the world is Gaussian, the model is valid, and the system is stable, both filters produce the same state estimate — but by entirely different mechanisms and for entirely different reasons. This is convergent optimality: two optimal solutions to different problems that agree when their domains of applicability coincide. The UKF is not a degenerate or limiting case of the ESPF. It is the uniquely optimal answer to its own well-posed problem. The ESPF is the uniquely optimal answer to a different well-posed problem [15]. The mathematical fact that reduces to in the Gaussian limit is a statement about the Hölder functional evaluated under Gaussian -cut geometry — not a statement that the UKF is doing a special case of what the ESPF does.
